{"word":"θάλασσα","slug":"θάλασσα","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b><el>ϑάλασσα, ης, ἡ</el></b> [<a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ etym.\">etym.</a> unknown]<b><p class=\"pp1\"/>—<pp>1.</pp> sea <a href='B:470 18:6'>Mt 18:6</a>; <a href='B:470 23:15'>23:15</a>; <a href='B:480 9:42'>Mk 9:42</a>; <a href='B:490 17:2'>Lk 17:2</a>, <a href='B:490 17:6'>6</a>; <a href='B:510 4:24'>Ac 4:24</a>; <a href='B:520 9:27'>Ro 9:27</a>; <a href='B:540 11:26'>2 Cor 11:26</a>; <a href='B:660 1:6'>Js 1:6</a>; <a href='B:720 1:1'>Jd 13</a>;</b> of the Red Sea<b> <a href='B:510 7:36'>Ac 7:36</a>; <a href='B:650 11:29'>Hb 11:29</a>;</b> <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ cp.\">cp.</a> <b><a href='B:530 10:1'>1 Cor 10:1f</a>;</b> of the Mediterranean Sea <b><a href='B:510 10:6'>Ac 10:6</a></b> <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ al.\">al.</a> <b><p class=\"pp1\"/>—<pp>2.</pp></b> of an inland body of water <b>lake:</b> <el>ϑ. τῆς Γαλιλαίας</el> Lake (Sea) of Galilee <b><a href='B:470 4:18'>Mt 4:18</a>; <a href='B:470 15:29'>15:29</a>; <a href='B:480 1:16'>Mk 1:16</a>; <a href='B:480 7:31'>7:31</a>;</b> <el>ϑ. τῆς Τιβεριάδος</el> Lake of Tiberias<b> <a href='B:500 21:1'>J 21:1</a></b> (<a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ cp.\">cp.</a> <b><a href='B:500 6:1'>6:1</a></b>); both terms = Lake Gennesaret (<a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ s.\">s.</a> <a href='B:490 5:1'>Lk 5:1</a>, where the author accurately uses the term <el><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:λίμνη\">λίμνη</a></el>). Occasionally without qualifier in <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ ref.\">ref.</a> to L. of G. <b><a href='B:470 8:24'>Mt 8:24</a>; <a href='B:470 13:1'>13:1</a>; <a href='B:470 14:24'>14:24</a> <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ v.l.\">v.l.</a>, 25f; <a href='B:480 2:13'>Mk 2:13</a>; <a href='B:480 3:7'>3:7</a></b> <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ al.\">al.</a> <center id=\"nav_bottom\"> <a id=\"left_arrow\" href=\"S:Θαδδαῖος\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> <a id=\"bottom_home\" href=\"S:#1.Table of Contents\">&emsp;&emsp;</a> <a id=\"right_arrow\" href=\"S:θά